Before changing UI, read:
- `docs/DESIGN.md`
- `docs/DESIGN_PRINCIPLES.md`
- `docs/USER_FLOWS.md`

Rules:
- Build mobile-first.
- Keep the UI premium, sharp, trustworthy, data-rich, fashion-aware, and consistent.
- Show the decision first, then the details.
- Prefer existing reusable components before creating new ones.
- Product cards show image, brand, name, SKU, Eazy Score, Community Score, and lowest price.
- Product detail must clearly compare Eazy Score, Community Score, and My Rating.
- Use the visual tokens in `docs/DESIGN_PRINCIPLES.md` unless the task explicitly changes the system.
- Avoid generic ecommerce UI, childish sneaker-store styling, crowded dashboards, and screen-by-screen visual drift.
- Include loading, empty, and error states for data screens.
- Do not invent new rating categories.
- Do not overbuild Feed before Browse, Product Detail, and Rating work.
